menu "Smart Pill Bottle (Farda)"

    config SPB_DEBUG_BUILD
        bool "Build with debug command surface (READ_LOG_FILE, GATTS DB dump)"
        default y
        help
            B5 build hygiene gate. When enabled, the firmware compiles in the
            debug-only BLE commands (READ_LOG_FILE 0x33, DELETE_LOG_FILE 0x34)
            and the GATTS database dump routine. Production / release images
            MUST set this to n (see sdkconfig.defaults.prod) so the debug
            surface is stripped from the binary entirely.

    config SPB_REQUIRE_TLS
        bool "Reject plaintext API targets (require https/mqtts)"
        default y
        help
            B3 transport hardening. When enabled, SET_API_TARGET rejects any
            target whose scheme is not https:// or mqtts://, and the telemetry
            client fails closed if server certificate verification cannot be
            performed. Disable ONLY for isolated bench testing.

    config SPB_RESTRICT_API_DOMAIN
        bool "Restrict SET_API_TARGET to allowed backend domain(s)"
        default y
        help
            B3. When enabled, SET_API_TARGET only accepts hosts that match the
            allow-list compiled into board_config.h (the Farda backend
            domain). Prevents redirecting telemetry to an attacker host.

endmenu
